ect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item" style="display: block; position: relative; background-image: none; background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/NEW_2147.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/NEW_2147.jpg" alt="" style="left: -80px;"> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><div style="clear:both;"></div></ul></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-prev" style="overflow: hidden; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: url(&quot;https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/arrows-32-32-1.png&quot;) left top no-repeat; display: block;"></div><div class="amazingcarousel-next" style="overflow: hidden; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: url(&quot;https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/arrows-32-32-1.png&quot;) right top no-repeat; display: block;"></div></div></div></div></div><p><strong>Features:</strong></p><p>The most distinguished feature of this corset is the scalloped edges in the neckline and the bottom.</p><p>There were several reasons, which motivated me to prepare this course:</p><p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;large number of orders for such corsets.</p><p>2. the unwillingness of the clients to adequately pay for the extra laborious work of making the scalloped corset. Therefore, in this course I will teach you a simple, an easy and yet a fast technique to sew the corset with scalloped edges and at the same times a technique that helps to achieve the desired result.</p><p>The use of my technique will turn the sewing of such complex corset into the budget option, which will be beneficial for you and your client!</p><p><strong>Where to use:</strong></p><ul><li>Perfect for sewing wedding dresses&nbsp;or evening garments;</li><li>Garments made with&nbsp;this technology are suitable for any body type and size;</li><li>Great for reshaping silhouettes and creating proportional forms.</li></ul><p><strong>Author:</strong>&nbsp;Tatiana Kozorovitsky</p><p><strong>Total length:</strong>&nbsp;4h 30m</p></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="transcript"><div class="overlay"></div><div itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"> <span itemprop="publisher" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Organization"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy"> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="text" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="https://www.facebook.com/corsetacademy"> </span> <span itemprop="author" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tatiana Kozorovitsky"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="width" content="128"><meta itemprop="height" content="128"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/jpeg"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/author/infocorsetacademy-net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="http://www.corsetacademy.net"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-12-sewing-the-remaining-lining-pieces/"><meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-12-sewing-the-remaining-lining-pieces/"><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2019-01-04T15:21:09+00:00"><meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2019-01-04T15:21:09+00:00"><meta itemprop="copyrightYear" content="2019"><meta itemprop="inLanguage" content="en_US"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tutorial 12. Sewing the remaining lining pieces."><meta itemprop="headline" content="Tutorial 12. Sewing the remaining lining pieces."><meta itemprop="description" content="I stitch together both halves of the central and the side pieces of the lining of the corset back."><meta itemprop="articleSection" content="Fantasy Corset"><meta itemprop="keywords" content="fantasy corset, video"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><div itemprop="articleBody"><h1><strong>Tutorial 12. Sewing the remaining lining pieces. </strong></h1><p><strong>I stitch together both halves of the central and the side pieces of the lining of the corset back. &nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image002.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="268"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image004.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="273"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image006.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="261"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image008.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="269"></p><p><strong>I cut seam allowances at an angle and topstitch. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image010.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="252"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image012.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="356"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image014.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="294"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image016.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="297"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image018.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="309"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image020.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="335"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image022.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="237"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image024.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="326"></p><p><strong>It is compulsory to check the quality of stitching. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image026.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="414"></p><p><strong>On the three sides of each half of the back lining - on the top, along the central cut and at the bottom, I make stay-stitching at a distance of 1.2 cm from the edge.</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image028.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="411"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image030.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="290"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image032.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="260"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image034.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="355"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image036.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="388"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image038.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="235"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image040.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="272"></p><p><strong>I stitch the wide Rigilene bones to the lining of the corset back. </strong></p><p><strong>I stitch three vertical bones in the place of lacing. </strong>The first bone is stitched along the stay-stitching on the central cut of the back lining in 1 mm from the stay-stitching. The upper and the lower ends of the bone are in 2 -3 mm to the stay-stitching of the back cuts. The second and third bones of the lacing are stitched parallel to the first bone very close to each other. I sew all the bones with two parallel stitches and I make bar tacks at the beginning and at the end of the stitches. I would like to emphasize that I begin and finish sewing of all the bones on the corset with a bar tack.</p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image042.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="378"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image044.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="349"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image046.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="326"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image048.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="315"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image050.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="255"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image052.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="349"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image054.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="258"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image056.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="297"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image058.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="282"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image060.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="329"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image062.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="296"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image064.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="278"></p><p><strong>I stitch the wide Rigilene bone along the back curve </strong>in a distance from stay-stitching in the upper and the lower cuts, which is equal to the stitched bones of the lacing.</p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image066.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="303"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image068.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="269"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image070.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="286"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image072.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="291"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image074.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="315"></p><p><strong>I stitch the wide Rigilene bone to the back side piece in the bone marking.&nbsp; </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image076.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="306"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image078.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="280"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image080.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="281"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image082.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="286"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image084.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="310"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image086.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="305"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Thus, all bones on the first half of the lining of the corset back are attached. </strong>I have made a mistake while sewing the bones – I did not press the bones i.e. I did not flatten them, so it complicated significantly my work. During stitching of the non-pressed bones the pieces are twisted and thread often tears. I recommend pressing bones with a hot iron before stitching the Rigilene bones.</p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image088.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="381"></p><p><strong>This is how the pressed half of the back lining with the bones looks.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image090.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="382"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image092.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="347"></p><p><strong>I stitch the wide Rigilene bones on the second half of the back. The bones are pressed.&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Now I stitch the lacing bones. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image094.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="245"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image096.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="247"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image098.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="307"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image100.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="288"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image102.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="299"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image104.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="311"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image106.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="296"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image108.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="300"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>I stitch a bone along the back curve. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image110.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="294"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image112.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="311"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image114.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="261"></p><p><strong>I stitch the bone on the back side piece. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image116.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="266"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image118.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="349"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image120.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="251"></p><p><strong>So, I have also attached all bones to the back second half of the lining. </strong>It is obviously faster and easier to attach the iron-pressed bones.</p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image122.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="428"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image124.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="433"></p><p><strong>Now I just need to stitch the vertical bones in the lining of the front side pieces. </strong></p><p>At the beginning I made stay-stitching along the top of the pieces, and then I stitch the thin Rigilene bone down to the bottom of the piece along the bone marking in some millimeters from stay-stitching.</p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image126.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="280"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image128.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="277"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image130.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="253"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image132.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="293"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image134.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="318"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image136.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="288"></p><p><strong>I attach the vertical bone on the second side piece of the front. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image138.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="267"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image140.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="251"></p><p><strong>I stitch together the side seams of the lining, i.e. I baste the side pieces of the back and the front. </strong>The back side piece is shorter than the front side piece, where there is the notch, showing the level of the side seam.</p><p><strong>The side seam is made till the stay-stitching in the lower cut of the back.&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image142.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="247"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image144.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="337"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image146.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="266"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>I baste the second side seam of the corset lining. &nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image148.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="272"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image150.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="320"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image152.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="289"></p><p><strong>I cut seam allowances of the side seams at an angle and topstitch.&nbsp; </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image154.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="253"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image156.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="260"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image158.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="329"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image160.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="305"></p><p><strong>I topstitch the second side seam of the corset lining. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image162.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="302"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image164.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="288"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image166.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="270"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image168.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="288"></p><p><strong>I stitch the narrow Rigilene bones along the side seams. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image170.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="298"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image172.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="287"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image174.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="313"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image176.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="329"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image178.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="260"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image180.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="299"></p><p><strong>I attach the bone along the second side seam. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image182.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="299"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image184.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="266"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image186.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="259"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image188.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="347"></p><p><strong>Before stitching the pieces of the lining along the front middle curves, it is necessary to pay attention to the cuts of the front middle pieces between the under bust and the bust lines.</strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image190.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="223"></p><p><strong>I decided to trim in order to slightly straighten these areas, so that to make the middle curves to look more elegant. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image192.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="292"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image194.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="259"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image196.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="298"></p><p><strong>I stitch together the pieces of the corset lining along the middle curves. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image198.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="302"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image200.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="289"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image202.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="270"></p><p><strong>I cut seam allowance of the middle curve at an angle and topstitch. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image204.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="418"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image206.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="472"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image208.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="267"></p><p><strong>I baste and topstitch the second front middle curve of the lining. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image210.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="282"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image212.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="323"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image214.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="303"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image216.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="306"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image218.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="290"></p><p><strong>I attach the narrow Rigilene bone along the front middle curves of the lining. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image220.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="291"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image222.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="304"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image224.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="266"></p><p><strong>I attach the bones along the second middle curve of the corset front. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image226.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="289"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image228.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="302"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image230.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="269"></p><p><strong>Therefore, all vertical curves of the corset lining are basted and bones are attached along them. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image232.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="347"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Now I can stitch the horizontal narrow Rigilene bone in the upper cut of the corset lining, </strong>starting from the corner of the neckline to the central cut of the back. I slightly gather the bone and sew it up, measuring 1 mm from stay-stitching along the armscye. In the areas of the armscyes, I ease in the fabric for a better fit of the corset in the armpit.</p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image234.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="448"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image236.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="333"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image238.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="296"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image240.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="274"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image242.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="287"></p><p><strong>I stitch the horizontal bone in the upper cut of the lining from the second side of the corset. </strong></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image244.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="243"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image246.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="347"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image248.jpg" alt="" width="617" height="338"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image250.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="287"></p><p><img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%2012.files/image252.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="281"></p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="pattern"><p>Sewing patterns are in PDF format.</p><p>To print sewing patterns open the files, press “print” and choose “<strong>PRINT IN ACTUAL SIZE</strong>“.</p><p>The pattern is divided to A4 paper sheets for home printer.</p> <a 